> I would subtract 10% for JVM overhead. @fnothaft?

10% would definitely be overkill unless you're doing mad off-heap allocation in the JVM. IIRC, JVM overhead is O(100MB), so for a large heap allocation, JVM overhead is in the wash. When running Spark, which does a ton of off-heap allocation post-1.5.x, I'd give about 8g overhead per 200g heap, but that's very much a special case.

